<p><span style="font-size:110%;"><span style="font-family: 'Berkshire Swash', cursive;"><strong>A Letter From the Author:</strong></span></span><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;</span>&quot;Someone once told me that they had a pet peeve about hubs that didn't explain what they were about. I didn't like putting anything up at the top, so I decided to end this hub with a small little letter. So, what is&#8230; Vend-a-Friend?<br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;</span>&quot;Vend-a-Friend is a story about a character, named Brainy Brian, who might really not be the good guy. He's no hero, he does a lot of bad things&#8230; but he does some good things too. He's just&#8230; a guy. Really. And he starts as an employee at Dr. Wondertainment, but quickly gets thrust into the 'real world', and soon after, the anomalous world. When I started writing this, I didn't expect it to get to be the length of a real novel. I mean, Christ, this is over 60,000 words long! It was supposed to end after five chapters, but it just&#8230; kept going. It's officially over, now that it's fifteen chapters long, but man did it go on and on.<br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;</span>&quot;When I started writing this, the goal was to make a dark Dr. Wondertainment series. Well, that had been done before. So then it became to redesign all of Dr. Wondertainment, because I wasn't happy with any headcanons of Dr. Wondertainment on the site. I did that, and then it just became&#8230; well, an exercise in actually writing a big long story! This is, at the time of writing, the longest thing I have ever written. I mean, it's a proper&#8230; story. And that's insane. It's probably my proudest work as well, because people have enjoyed it. I got to flex my characterization muscles, see how I handled an overarching plot, <em>tons</em> of worldbuilding for a world that I just <em>adored</em> writing in (and will likely return to), and most of all I just had&#8230; so much gosh darn fun with this one.<br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;</span>&quot;And did I handle all of this well?<br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;</span>&quot;Holy heck, who even knows. You tell me. My guess is that it's pretty clearly amateurish. I mean, jeez, this is my first story longer than three parts <em>ever</em>. So. There. That's what this hub is about.<br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;</span>&quot;Enjoy.&quot;</p>



